ools, allocation is of Rs. 1,500 crore while for Natural Calamities Fund is Rs. 2,002 crore and YSR-PM Fasal Bima Yojana is Rs. 1,163 crore.For the AP mid-day meal scheme, govt. has allotted Rs. 1,077 crore. Accordingly, a sum of Rs. 1,500 crore has been earmarked for infrastructure development in hospitals. To provide subsidized rice under the public distribution system, a sum of Rs. 3,000 crore is allocated. For the development of the capital city of Amaravati, the state government has proposed to allocate Rs. 500 crore in the Budget.The estimated revenue deficit of AP Budget 2019-20 is about Rs. 1,778 crore while the fiscal deficit is estimated at Rs. 35,260 crore.  Sarkari Yojana App - Download Now Source / Reference Link: https://www.aninews.in/news/national/general-news/andhra-pradesh-jaganmohan-governments-first-budget-focuses-on-housing-agriculture20190712165115/  at  "}